1.Rule 1: Consistency
a.equals(b) == true -> a.hashCode() === b.hashCode();


2. Symmetry
a.equals(b) === true <-> b.equals(a) === true;


3. Transitive
if a.equals(b) && b.equals(c) -> a.equals(c)


4. Reflexivity
a.equals(a) === true // object must equals to itself


5. Non-null
a.equals(null) == false // no object equals null


Example
class BrokenPerson{
    String name;
    int age;

    public BrokenPerson(String name, int age){
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }

    // Only equals() without hashCode() - Breaks the contract!
    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object obj){
        if(this == obj) return true;
        if(obj == null || getClass() != obj.getClass()) return false;
        BrokenPerson that = (BrokenPerson) obj;
        return age == that.age && Object.equals(name, that.name);
    }

    Missing hashCode implementation

    take note always Override .equals and hashCode()
}





